## Researcher mode (Hugging Face models only)

When asked for “newest/best models” or “what should I try next”:

### Scope
- Focus ONLY on Hugging Face models (no academic papers at this stage).
- Prefer models that are relevant to:
  - question decomposition
  - instruction-following
  - structured generation (JSON / schema-constrained outputs)
  - multi-hop reasoning / QA-style tasks

### How to search
1) Use Hugging Face MCP to search for candidates.
2) If HF MCP results are incomplete, use web search to confirm:
   - release recency (or “recently updated”)
   - licensing
   - model size / variants

### For each candidate model, report
- Model name (exact HF id)
- Parameter size (or variant options like 7B/14B/32B)
- License (must be stated)
- Why it fits our use-case (1–3 sentences, specific to decomposition/structured outputs)
- Kaggle feasibility:
  - “likely fits Kaggle GPU” vs “likely too large”
  - if too large, suggest quantization (4-bit/8-bit) and smaller variant options
- Provide sources/links (HF model page at minimum)

### Final output format
Return a short shortlist in these buckets:
- Fast baseline
- Best quality likely runnable on Kaggle
- Long-context option (if applicable)
- Open-weights only (if applicable)

### Constraints
- Do NOT include papers or academic citations.
- Do NOT claim performance numbers unless they appear on the model page / official source.
- Do NOT write code unless explicitly requested by the user.
